[Event "Baker Bridge - Roman Key Card Blackwood"]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "S:A63.AK9865.K.A32 QJ52.7.9643.Q864 K7.QJ3.AQJT875.K T984.T42.2.JT975"]
[Declarer "N"]
[Contract "7NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
1H pass 2D pass 3H pass 4NT pass 5C pass 5NT pass 6D pass 7NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: N, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:0, nBasis: 2, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "1179ea27800a993cb2bfe45b4808ea07a1563f441b3b7a6aa517b5dafe8919cb"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/roman_keycard"]
[Student "S"]
{The bidding has been as shown. Yes, you could have jump-shifted on your first bid.  

Slam in \Hs is almost certain, but you should check for Key-Cards. You bid 4NT and partner says 5\C.  

Partner shows 1 or 4 Key-cards. Since he jumped on the second round you figure it must be 4. So you have all the Key-Cards. Time to find out about the other Kings, so you bid 5NT. Partner replies 6\D.  

Partner has 1 King, the only one left, the \DK. You can count about 17 high-card tricks available so you bid 7NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
