1H pass 3S pass 4NT pass 6H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "ef0013671b8756a62d2b762ac94af06713c33e1fdbd4828019ea017a34225923"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/roman_keycard"]
[Student "S"]
{Your 3\S bid is a Splinter, agreeing \Hs as trump, and showing opening hand strength with a singleton or void in \Ss.  

You have one Key-Card, the \HA. You also have a \S void, but since bidding 6\S would take you above the 6\H level you just respond 6\H. Partner will deduce that your void is in \Ss, particularly because you Splintered in that suit. Partner passes your 6\H bid.}

